  "original_title": "\u0b87\u0bb2\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc8\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc6\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bbe\u0ba9 \u0bae\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0bb2\u0bbe\u0bb5\u0ba4\u0bc1 \u0b9f\u0bc6\u0bb8\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0bae\u0bc1\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0ba9\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bc8\u0baf\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0b85\u0bb5\u0bc1\u0bb8\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bc7\u0bb2\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bbe",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Australia lead in first Test against Sri Lanka",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Australia's presence at the end of the second day of the first match of the two - match Test series against Sri Lanka, which started yesterday in Galle.",
        "Sri Lanka, who batted first in the match, lost all their wickets in their first innings and scored 212 runs.",
        "Currently on the field, skipper Per Cummins is unbeaten on 26 and Nathan Lyon on eight. Earlier, Cameron Green scored 77, Usman Khawaja 71, Alex Carey 45 and David Warner 25. In bowling, Ramesh Mendis 4, Jeffrey Wandersay 2, Tananjaya de Silva took one wicket.",
        "Sri Lanka: 212/10 (Batting: Niroshan Dickwella 58, Anjalo Mathews 39, Timothy Karunaratne 28, Padum Nisanga 23, Ramesh Mendis 22, Tananjaya de Silva 14. Bowling: Nathan Lyon 5/90, Mitchell Swabson 3/55, Per Cummins. 1/25, Michelle Stark 1/31)",
        "Australia: 313/8 (Cricketers: Cameron Green 77, Usman Kawaja 71, Alex Carey 45, Per Cummins IE 26, David Warner 25. Bowling: Ramesh Mendis 4/107, Jeffrey Wandersay 2/68, Tananjaya de Silva 1). / 8)"
      ],
